[[File:Ancient Wyvern icon.png|left]]
'''Ancient Wyverns''' are [[Slayer monsters]] that require a [[Slayer]] level of 82 in order to be harmed. They reside in the [[Wyvern Cave]] on [[Fossil Island]] and are the strongest species of Wyvern in ''Old School RuneScape''. Like with other [[Wyverns]], an [[elemental shield|elemental]], [[mind shield|mind]], [[dragonfire shield|dragonfire]] or [[ancient wyvern shield]] provides significant protection against their [[icy breath]]. These monsters require completion of the [[Bone Voyage]] quest to be assigned as a Slayer task.

In addition to being harder to fight, Ancient Wyverns share the ability with [[Taloned Wyvern]]s to use an unblockable [[Ranged]] attack that resembles a lighter coloured [[Water Blast]]. This attack ignores [[Protection prayers]] and hits around 10, though they can also miss. They also appear to use all [[Melee]] attack types. When fighting them, the highest defensive [[armour]] the player can access is best suited to use against them. Should one choose to use range to fight them, it is recommended to fight in melee range and use Protect from Melee after de-aggroing the Wyverns.

Auto aggression can be removed if one gains aggression from one Wyvern, waits 10-15 minutes north of the third mushroom on the narrow high path, and then kills the aggroed Wyvern.

